<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-011-214 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 477 146</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Nov 14 1991 n1804* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (UK) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A 31% fall in computer peripherals unit helps FKI net profit down36% to #9.7m. (FKI PLC's Cutting Tools and Computer Peripheralsdivisions experience losses)(pounds sterling)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   FKI PLC (Finance).andO;Topic:     Subsidiary CompaniesFinancial ReportLosses.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>A 31% FALL IN COMPUTER PERIPHERALS UNIT HELPSandM;FKI NET PROFIT DOWN 36% TO #9.7mandM;FKI Plc saw interim net profits for the year to September 30 plummet to #9.7mfrom #15.1m on turnover that fell to #371.1m from #389m last year.andP;  TheAutomation Group's profits fell significantly to #5.4m with sales down by16%.andP;  FKI says that this is due to very depressed market conditions in theUK, and the Cutting Tools and Computer Peripherals divisions experienced a31% drop in sales.andP;  However, Process Control activities performed well withprogress being made on the Australian Swanbank's power project, theintroduction of telemetry products and the finalisation of a joint marketingand technical development collaboration agreement with Honeywell.andP;  FKI'sother divisions - Transportation and Engineering - contributed #3.7m and#11.1m respectively to profitability.andP;  Profits from transportation fellsharply from #9.3m, and FKI attributes this to lower sales volumes in USautomotive activities.andP;  Engineering is said to have achieved a creditableperformance despite lower sales.andP;  The share price took one look at thefigures and turned tail, off 7.5 pence at 51 pence.andO;</TEXT></DOC>